<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFLabinger_JA.2C_Weininger_SJ2005">Labinger JA, Weininger SJ (2005). "Controversy in chemistry: how do you prove a negative?—the cases of phlogiston and cold fusion". <i>Angew Chem Int Ed Engl</i> <b>44</b> (13): 1916–22. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1002%2Fanie.200462084" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1002%2Fanie.200462084" rel="nofollow">10.1002/anie.200462084</a></span>.  "So there matters stand: no cold fusion researcher has been able to dispel the stigma of 'pathological science' by rigorously and reproducibly demonstrating effects sufficiently large to exclude the possibility of error (for example, by constructing a working power generator), nor does it seem possible to conclude unequivocally that all the apparently anomalous behavior can be attributed to error.".</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Controversy+in+chemistry%3A+how+do+you+prove+a+negative%3F%E2%80%94the+cases+of+phlogiston+and+cold+fusion&amp;rft.jtitle=Angew+Chem+Int+Ed+Engl&amp;rft.aulast=Labinger+JA%2C+Weininger+SJ&amp;rft.au=Labinger+JA%2C+Weininger+SJ&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.volume=44&amp;rft.issue=13&amp;rft.pages=1916%E2%80%9322&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1002%2Fanie.200462084&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Pathological_science"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="DOE2004r">U.S. Department of Energy (2004), <i><a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20070114122346/http://www.science.doe.gov/Sub/Newsroom/News_Releases/DOE-SC/2004/low_energy/CF_Final_120104.pdf" class="external text" title="http://web.archive.org/web/20070114122346/http://www.science.doe.gov/Sub/Newsroom/News_Releases/DOE-SC/2004/low_energy/CF_Final_120104.pdf" rel="nofollow">Report of the Review of Low Energy Nuclear Reactions</a></i>, Washington, DC: doe.gov<span class="printonly">, <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20070114122346/http://www.science.doe.gov/Sub/Newsroom/News_Releases/DOE-SC/2004/low_energy/CF_Final_120104.pdf" class="external free" title="http://web.archive.org/web/20070114122346/http://www.science.doe.gov/Sub/Newsroom/News_Releases/DOE-SC/2004/low_energy/CF_Final_120104.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://web.archive.org/web/20070114122346/http://www.science.doe.gov/Sub/Newsroom/News_Releases/DOE-SC/2004/low_energy/CF_Final_120104.pdf</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved on 2008-07-19</span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Report+of+the+Review+of+Low+Energy+Nuclear+Reactions&amp;rft.aulast=U.S.+Department+of+Energy&amp;rft.au=U.S.+Department+of+Energy&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.place=Washington%2C+DC&amp;rft.pub=doe.gov&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20070114122346%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.doe.gov%2FSub%2FNewsroom%2FNews_Releases%2FDOE-SC%2F2004%2Flow_energy%2FCF_Final_120104.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Pathological_science"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>.</li>
